Story: Create a webserver that handles 404 errors

Given:
  port: Integer = 8080
  server_socket: Socket

Step 1 → Create server_socket on port
  Effect: Create socket server_socket on port
  Because: Start HTTP server

Step 2 → Accept connection on server_socket
  Effect: Accept connection on server_socket
  Because: Handle client request

Step 3 → Read request
  Effect: Network read
  Because: Get HTTP request from client
  Then: request becomes parse HTTP request from request_data

Step 4 → If request.url = "/", go to Step 5
  Because: Valid route exists
  Otherwise: go to Step 6

Step 5 → Send success response
  Effect: Send "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\n\r\n<h1>Welcome</h1>" to client
  Because: Return valid page content
  Then: go to Step 7

Step 6 → Send 404 error response
  Effect: Send "HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\n\r\n<h1>404 - Page Not Found</h1>" to client
  Because: Handle invalid route with proper error

Step 7 → If TRUE, repeat from Step 2
  Because: Continue serving requests
  Otherwise: go to End

Error:
  Return "Server crashed"
  Effect: Print "Server error occurred"
  Because: Handle unexpected server failure

End: Return "Server stopped"
